    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1777"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1777">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/48.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Price</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 12, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your July 8. You are instructed to inform Minister for Foreign Affairs that as
                    the American Minister at Panama is fully conversant with all details of the
                    wireless telegraph agreement and is able to communicate promptly with the
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs, this Government feels it more desirable to
                    continue to handle the matter through the American Legation at Panama.</p>
                <p>You may add that the Department will, of course, always be pleased to consider
                    any comments that Doctor Morales may care to make.</p>
                <p>You are instructed to request formally again a written reply from Señor Lefevre
                    to your notes on the wireless telegraph agreement. Continue to report by
                    cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John E. Osborne</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
